Yabai window management script: Move window to the right space (next space) with automatic space creation at edge. This script is part of a comprehensive macOS window management system using Yabai. It intelligently moves the focused window to the next space on the current display, creating a new space if the window is at the rightmost edge. Features include robust error handling, detailed logging through a centralized log_helper.sh system, state tracking before/after operations, and automatic window refocusing after movement. The script handles edge cases like null window IDs and ensures windows remain focused after space transitions. It's designed to work seamlessly with keyboard shortcuts via Karabiner-Elements for rapid window organization workflows.
